author: ANDREW MILLER Sports Writer
title: Lady Hounds blanked by Greencastle
text:
PHOTOS BY MICKEY NYE Morehouse 
Junior midfielder Rachel Morehouse settles a ball with her first touch during the Hounds’ clash with the Greencastle Blue Devils Thursday. Bender 
Shippensburg defender Maddie Bender wins the ball from a Greencastle attacker Thursday. Strohm 
Junior forward Sarah Strohm fends off a Greencastle defender during Shippensburg’s 2-0 loss at Greencastle’s Kaley Field. Posted: Tuesday, October 6, 2015 6:00 am Lady Hounds blanked by Greencastle By ANDREW MILLER Sports Writer ShipNC.com | 0 comments 
The vast improvement made by the Lady Greyhound soccer team may not yet be quantified by the club’s win and losses, but rather by goal differential. 
The Greyhounds fell in the first meeting to the Greencastle Blue Devils by a lopsided 9-1 final score.
